structured.title: Family Discusses Church Hospitality And Time Off
structured.overview: The user talks through several topics at home, including reviewing last yearâ€™s financial accounts and trying to interpret entries in a pension pot (unsure if certain amounts are cash deposits). The conversation shifts to church hospitality team matters: Sarah, Sophie, Debbie, Gay, Denise, Lois, Ronnie, and the user are mentioned as part of or related to the hospitality group. Lois led a recent meeting, raised concerns about serving drinks at the end of services because it delays packing up, and there was some tension around the idea of a suggestion box, perceived as discouraging open feedback. They also discuss the need to build up the team so that Steve and the user can take a week off in April and have one Sunday a month from April where they are not serving. The user considers asking their mum to re-engage with running hospitality, though she previously said she didnâ€™t want to be involved. Interspersed are family interactions with children (Jude and Eddie), including pausing a match on TV, giving snacks, and asking them to bring dishes back to the kitchen and not leave mess for others.

## Pension and account queries
- User unsure about pension pot transactions
- Mentions large deposits around 7 September and 1 March
- Unclear memory of paying over Â£1,000 in

## Hospitality team meeting
- Hospitality team includes Sarah, Sophie, Debbie, Gay, Denise, Lois, Ronnie, user
- Lois leads meeting; generally seen as doing good job
- Some cattiness around idea of a suggestion box

## Serving drinks and service flow
- Lois suggests stopping drink service at end of service
- User says they never serve drinks then; others disagree
- Debbie notes user often chatting elsewhere, misses what happens

## Team capacity and time off
- Aim for Steve and user to have a week off in April
- Need to build team strength before April
- Plan: from April, team not serving once a month

## Possible help from user's mum
- Userâ€™s mum previously ran hospitality
- She currently doesnâ€™t want to be involved
- User considering asking her again privately

## Family and household interactions
- User coordinating with Jude about pausing match
- Asking Jude to join in kitchen after finishing
- Reminds Jude to bring bowl and crisps to kitchen

## Next steps
- Clarify unexplained pension deposits around specific dates
- Build hospitality team to allow April week off
- User to consider re-approaching mum about helping again
